  "remarks": "After the capture of the city of Mariupol by the Russian armed forces, the so-called “Head of the Donetsk People’s Republic” Denis Pushilin appointed Konstantin Ivashchenko mayor of Mariupol on 6 April 2022. He was dismissed in January 2023. He publicly supported and participated in the preparations for the illegal referenda in the occupied regions of Ukraine.",
